      • getEntity

        TGEntity getEntity(TGKey tgkey,
                   TGQueryOption option)
            throws TGException
        Get an Entity given an UniqueKey for the Object. If there are more than one entries, then the first one in the list is returned. The key needs to have all the attributes set for which the index is defined. see defining index for a Node, Edge or a Graph This is synchronous non transactional operation. It does not hold any locks.
        Parameters:
        tgkey - - An instance of a key using @see com.tibco.tgdb.TGGraphObjectFactory.createCompositeKey
        option - - properties affect the request such as batchsize, fetchsize and traversaldepth
        Returns:
        TGEntity for the key specified
        Throws:
        TGException - Throws an exception if there was any error while retrieving the object

      • updateEntity

        void updateEntity(TGEntity entity)
           throws TGException
        Mark an Entity for Update operation. Call this method to associate the entity with a Connection When commit is called, the object is resolved to check if it is dirty. Entity.setAttribute calls make the entity dirty. If it is dirty, then the object is send to the server for update, otherwise it is ignored. Calling multiple times, does not change the behavior. The same entity cannot be updated on multiple connections. It will throw a TGException of already associated to a connection.
        Parameters:
        entity - - The entity that was updated
        Throws:
        TGException - Throws an exception if there was any error while updating the object

      • deleteEntity

      • executeQuery

        TGResultSet executeQuery(java.lang.String expr,
                         TGQueryOption option)
                  throws TGException
        Execute an immediate Query with query options
        Parameters:
        expr - A subset of SQL-92 where clause. @see com.tibco.tgdb.query.TGQuery
        option - Query options for executing. Can be null, then it will use the default option
        Returns:
        A navigatable ResultSet if successful in executing the query. The result set will indicate errors if the query had any exceptions
        Throws:
        TGException - Throws an exception if there was any error while updating the object

      • executeQuery

        TGResultSet executeQuery(java.lang.String expr,
                         java.lang.String edgeFilter,
                         java.lang.String traversalCondition,
                         java.lang.String endCondition,
                         TGQueryOption option)
                  throws TGException
        Execute an immediate Query with query options The query option is place holder at this time
        Parameters:
        expr - A subset of SQL-92 where clause. @see com.tibco.tgdb.query.TGQuery
        edgeFilter - filter used for selecting edges to be returned
        traversalCondition - condition used for selecting edges to be traversed and returned
        endCondition - condition used to stop the traversal
        option - Query options for executing. Can be null, then it will use the default option
        Returns:
        A navigatable ResultSet if successful in executing the query. The result set will indicate errors if the query had any exceptions
        Throws:
        TGException - Throws an exception if there was any error while updating the object
